# Markdown the gate deliberately does not lint with prose rules:
#
#   - AGENTS.md, README.md — GENERATED from the .lex source (which `lexd check`
#     gates). These .md are the projection (bash tools/lex-convert-doc.sh) and
#     carry a "do not hand edit" preamble, so linting them is the generator's job.
#   - skills/ — agent-skill content, not prose. The files carry load-bearing
#     inline HTML tags (<what-to-do>, <prd-template>, …), language-less fences,
#     and fragment structure by design; markdownlint's prose rules miscategorize
#     them. They are vendored as a managed set, linted at their own source.
AGENTS.md
README.md
skills/
# docs/dev/pixi.md — same .lex-projection case as AGENTS.md/README.md: generated
# by `bash tools/lex-convert-doc.sh docs/dev/pixi.lex` (carries the "do not hand
# edit" preamble) and gated at its source by `lexd check`. lexd's section-number
# cross-references (`[see](#7)`) and label-colon section titles are valid Lex
# projection but markdownlint miscategorizes them (MD051/MD026), so it is linted
# at the .lex, not the .md.
docs/dev/pixi.md
